l.com/byline/masumi-goldman\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8b\",\"author-card-1\",{\"url\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/byline/laura-kasperzak\"}]]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"7f:[[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-0\",{\"children\":\"Kids, almost inevitably, can get in the way of a parent’s yoga practice—in our case, quite literally. Since yoga is such a significant part of our lives, and we both generally practice at home, it was only natural for us to invite our children on the mat. It wasn’t a hard sell—our kids wanted to be a part of our yoga, which was great and very welcome.\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8c\",\"inline-jw-0\",{\"type\":\"injectable\",\"disableAds\":false}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-1\",{\"children\":[\"If our kids are any indication, we at \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"http://www.twofitmoms.com\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Two Fit Moms\"}],\" think it’s likely that your kids would love to practice yoga with you. So this week, in honor of Mother’s Day, we are offering 6 tips for doing yoga with your kids.\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"h3\",\"h3-0\",{\"children\":\"1. Focus on the basics.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"figure\",\"figure-0\",{\"className\":\"pom-image-wrap alignnone\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L7a\",\"img-0\",{\"decoding\":\"async\",\"title\":\"Masumi doing Tree Pose with her kids.\",\"src\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/masumi-doing-tree-pose-with-her-kids.jpg?width=730\",\"alt\":\"Masumi doing Tree Pose with her kids.\",\"width\":1100,\"height\":400}]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-2\",{\"children\":[\"Kids love \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/downward-facing-dog/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Downward-Facing Dog\"}],\", \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/tree-pose/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Tree Pose\"}],\", \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-2\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/warrior-ii-pose/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Warrior II\"}],\", and \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-3\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/easy-pose/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Easy Pose\"}],\". These are great beginner poses, in general.\"]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-3\",{\"children\":\"Tree Pose is a great single-leg balance to practice with your children. Hold hands to link your trees together and create a forest. This is a fun way to help your kids balance while building their confidence in their abilities.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"$L8e\",\"in-content-leaderboard-0\",{\"className\":\"flex justify-center my-6 h-32\",\"id\":\"in-content-leaderboard-I0-P0-CMI0\",\"data-child-zone\":\"in-content-leaderboard-yj\"}],[\"$\",\"h3\",\"h3-1\",{\"children\":\"2. Let them surprise you.\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"figure\",\"figure-1\",{\"className\":\"pom-image-wrap alignnone\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L7a\",\"img-0\",{\"decoding\":\"async\",\"title\":\"Laura doing yoga with her daughter.\",\"src\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/laura-doing-yoga-with-her-daughter.jpg?width=730\",\"alt\":\"Laura doing yoga with her daughter.\",\"width\":1100,\"height\":400}]}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-4\",{\"children\":\"Teach them what they should be doing, and don’t fret if their poses aren’t perfect. Your kids may surprise you. This AcroYoga pose with my daughter did exactly that—I never expected her to get into this posture, and I don’t think she expected to either!\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-5\",{\"children\":\"Yoga with my daughter is all about having fun. But in between the giggles, I see glimmers of her own practice taking shape, which is very exciting for me to watch.\"}],\"\\n\",\"$L8f\",\"\\n\",\"$L90\",\"\\n\",\"$L91\",\"\\n\",\"$L92\",\"\\n\",\"$L93\",\"\\n\",\"$L94\",\"$L95\",\"\\n\",\"$L96\",\"\\n\",\"$L97\",\"\\n\",\"$L98\",\"\\n\",\"$L99\",\"\\n\",\"$L9a\",\"\\n\",\"$L9b\",\"\\n\",\"$L9c\",\"\\n\",\"$L9d\",\"\\n\",\"$L9e\",\"\\n\",\"$L9f\",\"\\n\",\"$La0\",\"\\n\"]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"80:[]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"8f:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-6\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"See also\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/slideshow/two-fit-moms-grounding-gravity-defying-earth-day-yoga-poses/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Two Fit Moms’ Gravity-Defying Earth Day Flow\"}]]}]\n90:[\"$\",\"h3\",\"h3-2\",{\"children\":\"3. Play with animal poses.\"}]\n91:[\"$\",\"figure\",\"figure-2\",{\"className\":\"pom-image-wrap alignnone\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L7a\",\"img-0\",{\"decoding\":\"async\",\"title\":\"Masumi Goldman doing Camel Pose with her kids.\",\"src\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/masumi-goldman-doing-camel-pose-with-her-kids.jpg?width=730\",\"alt\":\"Masumi Goldman doing Camel Pose with her kids.\",\"width\":1100,\"height\":400}]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"92:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-7\",{\"children\":[\"Consider focusing on the animal-named poses like \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/camel-pose/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Camel\"}],\", Butterfly (\",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/poses/bound-angle-pose-2/ \",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Bound Angle Pose\"}],\"), \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-2\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/poses/cobra-pose-2/ \",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Cobra\"}],\", \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-3\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/cat-pose/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Cat\"}],\"/\",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/pose/cow-pose/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Cow\"}],\", etc. These postures will resonate with them and are ones that will allow them to be more playful and silly.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"93:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-8\",{\"children\":\"Camel Pose is a challenging backbend, but the good news is that it can be modified for kids in the same way that it can be modified for adults. Begin in a kneeling position with the thighs perpendicular to the floor, place your hands onto your lower back, fingers pointed down. Lift your chest and create an even backbend, avoiding collapsing into the lower back. If your children would like to attempt the full expression of the pose, encourage them to first try the pose with their toes tucked and heels lifted. Slowly reach one hand back at a time to hold each heel. If that goes well, they can try the version with toes untucked. Whichever version they attempt, just make sure that they are safe and having a good time.\"}]\n94:[\"$\",\"$L8e\",\"in-content-leaderboard-1\",{\"className\":\"flex justify-center my-6 h-32\",\"id\":\"in-content-leaderboard-I1-P0-CMI0\",\"data-child-zone\":\"in-content-leaderboard-yj\"}]\n95:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-9\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"See also\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/slideshow/two-fit-moms-backbending-practice/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Two Fit Moms’ Backbending Practice\"}]]}]\n96:[\"$\",\"h3\",\"h3-3\",{\"children\":\"4. Add modifications to make it extra fun.\"}]\n97:[\"$\",\"figure\",\"figure-3\",{\"className\":\"pom-image-wrap alignnone\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L7a\",\"img-0\",{\"decoding\":\"async\",\"title\":\"Laura Kasperzak of Two Fit Moms doing yoga with her daughter.\",\"src\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/laura-kasperzak-of-two-fit-moms-doing-yoga-with-her-daughter.jpg?width=730\",\"alt\":\"Laura Kasperzak of Two Fit Moms doing yoga with her daughter.\",\"width\":1100,\"height\":400}]}]\n98:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-10\",{\"children\":[\"Kids are naturally flexible so they love \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/poses/cobra-pose-2/ \",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Cobra Pose\"}],\"—especially if you ask them to try to touch their toes to their head! Partnering with mom makes it extra fun.\"]}]\n99:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-11\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"See also\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/slideshow/two-fit-moms-heart-opening-partner-yoga/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Two Fit Moms’ Heart-Opening Partner Yoga Sequence\"}]]}]\n9a:[\"$\",\"h3\",\"h3-4\",{\"children\":\"5. Don’t expect them to do a full practice.\"}]\n9b:[\"$\",\"figure\",\"figure-4\",{\"className\":\"pom-image-wrap alignnone\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L7a\",\"img-0\",{\"decoding\":\"async\",\"title\":\"Masumi Goldman's kids doing Tree Pose.\",\"src\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/masumi-goldmans-kids-doing-tree-pose.jpg?width=730\",\"alt\":\"Masumi Goldman's kids doing Tree Pose.\",\"width\":1100,\"height\":400}]}]\n9c:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-12\",{\"children\":\"We know this sounds obvious, but when our kids started to join us, we thought they would just fall in love with yoga and practice for a full 30–45 minutes. WRONG. Children under the age of 10 do not typically have the attention span, but they can manage 5–10 minutes on the mat. So, start with small intervals of time.\"}]\n9d:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-13\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"See also\"}],[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/slideshow/good-morning-yoga-poses-jumpstart-kids-day/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"Good Morning Yoga: A 3-Minute Flow to Jumpstart Your Kids’ Day\"}]]}]\n9e:[\"$\",\"h3\",\"h3-5\",{\"children\":\"6. Get them their own yoga gear.\"}]\n9f:[\"$\",\"figure\",\"figure-5\",{\"className\":\"pom-image-wrap alignnone\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L7a\",\"img-0\",{\"decoding\":\"async\",\"title\":\"La"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"ura Kasperzak's kids practice yoga on Gaiam yoga mats for kids.\",\"src\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/laura-kasperzaks-kids-practice-yoga-on-gaiam-yoga-mats-for-kids.jpg?width=730\",\"alt\":\"Laura Kasperzak's kids practice yoga on Gaiam yoga mats for kids.\",\"width\":1100,\"height\":400}]}]\na0:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-14\",{\"children\":[\"We don’t know about your kids, but ours love to have their own space and their own stuff. Fun \",[\"$\",\"$L8d\",\"react-link-0\",{\"href\":\"https://www.yogajournal.com/lifestyle/kids-yoga-mats/\",\"data-afl-p\":\"0\",\"className\":\"article-content-link text-brand-primary underline hover:text-brand-primary/85 break-words overflow-wrap-anywhere\",\"children\":\"yoga mats for kids\"}],\" will make your little ones feel grown up—and you won’t have to share your mat!\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"a1:I[933085,[\"https://headless.yogajournal.com/_next/static/chunks/840844254684f8c8.js?dpl=dpl_9TGXkioRwxWPFY5xG1igJLeTKnmB\",\"https://headless.yogajournal.com/_next/static/chunks/d23f1a97844a5860.js?dpl=dpl_9TGXkioRwxWPFY5xG1igJLeTKnmB\",\"https://headless.yogajournal.com/_next/static/chunks/39e645a19a550081.js?dpl=dpl_9TGXkioRwxWPFY5xG1igJLeTKnmB\",\"https://headless.yogajournal.com/_next/static/chunks/bb7469dce8dc2433.js?dpl=dpl_9TGXkioRwxWPFY5xG1igJLeTKnmB\"],\"FollowButton\"]\n7b:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"fp-remove flex items-center justify-start gap-(--spacing-base-tight)\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"/byline/masumi-goldman\",\"data-outbound-instanced\":\"true\",\"className\":\"flex items-center justify-start gap-(--spacing-base-tight)\",\"aria-label\":\"View Masumi Goldman's bio\",\"children\":[\"\",[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-utility-2 font-bold text-primary\",\"children\":\"Masumi Goldman\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"$La1\",null,{\"location\":\"byline\",\"profileKey\":\"masumi-goldman\",\"pianoId\":\"article-author-follow-button\"}]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"7c:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"fp-remove flex items-center justify-start gap-(--spacing-base-tight)\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"/byline/laura-kasperzak\",\"data-outbound-instanced\":\"true\",\"className\":\"flex items-center justify-start gap-(--spacing-base-tight)\",\"aria-label\":\"View Laura Kasperzak's bio\",\"children\":[\"\",[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-utility-2 font-bold text-primary\",\"children\":\"Laura Kasperzak\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"$La1\",null,{\"location\":\"byline\",\"profileKey\":\"laura-kasperzak\",\"pianoId\":\"article-author-follow-button\"}]]}]\n"])</script></body></html>